<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="I" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Its" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Its,</orth> poss. pronoun of the 3<hi rend="sup">d</hi> person, relating to neuters; a word just coming into use in Shakespeare's time, but not nearly so frequent as <emph>his</emph> (q. v.): <bibl n="shak. tmp 1.2.95" default="NO" valid="yes">Tp. I, 2, 95</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tmp 1.2.95" default="NO" valid="yes">Tp. I, 2, 95</bibl> <bibl n="shak. mm 1.2.4" default="NO" valid="yes">Meas. I, 2, 4</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. wt 1.2.151" default="NO" valid="yes">Wint. I, 2, 151</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. wt 1.2.151" default="NO" valid="yes">Wint. I, 2, 151</bibl> <bibl n="shak. wt 1.2.151" default="NO" valid="yes">Wint. I, 2, 151</bibl> <bibl n="shak. wt 1.2.151" default="NO" valid="yes">Wint. I, 2, 151</bibl> <bibl n="shak. wt 3.3.46" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 3, 46</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 3.2.393" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B III, 2, 393</bibl>. The earlier O. Edd. <emph>it,</emph> the later <cit><quote>its:</quote> <bibl n="shak. tmp 2.1.163" default="NO" valid="yes">Tp. II, 1, 163</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. wt 2.3.178" default="NO" valid="yes">Wint. II, 3, 178</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h4 1.2.131" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B I, 2, 131</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h5 5.2.40" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 V, 2, 40</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. rom 1.3.52" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. I, 3, 52</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ham 1.2.216" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. I, 2, 216</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ham 5.1.244" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 1, 244</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lr 4.2.32" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. IV, 2, 32</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ant 2.7.49" default="NO" valid="yes">Ant. II, 7, 49</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ant 2.7.49" default="NO" valid="yes">Ant. II, 7, 49</bibl><lb />Even absolutely, contrary to the present use: <cit><quote>each following day became the next day's master, till the last made former wonders its,</quote> <bibl n="shak. h8 1.1.18" default="NO" valid="yes">H8 I, 1, 18</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>